1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 2999 By: Dobrinski
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to officers; prohibiting public
officials from being required to sign nondisclosure
8 agreements related to appointed or elected office;
providing for inapplicability of restriction based
9 upon matters unrelated to performance of duties of
public office; providing for codification; and
10 providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 401 of Title 51, unless there is
18 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. No elected or appointed public official shall be required to
20 sign any type of nondisclosure agreement with respect to a matter
21 involving the performance of duties by the public official if the
22 nondisclosure agreement relates to a project that would have
23 significant impact on the jurisdiction or jurisdictions in which the
24 project would be located or operate. As used in this subsection,
Req. No. 15094 Page 1

1 "sig nificant impact" means facilities or operations that would
2 affect electrical power usage, water, or other utility
3 infrastructure and similar factors for at least ten percent (10%) of
4 the residents of the area in which the project or facility is
5 proposed to be located or operated.
6 B. The provisions of this section shall not be applicable to a
7 nondisclosure agreement that a person is requested or required to
8 sign with respect to a matter which is personal or related to
9 litigation or potential litigation which does not involve the
10 performance of any duty imposed directly upon the person because of
11 the appointed or elected office the person occupies.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
